title: Get video data of a TikTok account

headers.name: Access-Token
headers.description: Access token authorized by TikTok creators. To obtain an access token, use /tt_user/oauth2/token/ .

parameters.name: business_id
parameters.description: Application specific unique identifier for the TikTok account. Pass the value of the open_id field returned in the response of /tt_user/oauth2/token/ to this field.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Requested fields. If not set, returns the default field only. Default value : ["item_id"] . If you want to request multiple fields, you need to at least include "item_id" in the value for fields . Otherwise, an error may occur. Example : ["item_id", "create_time"] . Note : All video engagement metrics are aggregated over the lifetime of the video. Unlike profile-level metrics, the aggregation is not limited to a 60-day look-back period. To retrieve certain fields in the response, you must have specific permissions. You can check the "Required permission" column for each field in the response schema to determine the permissions needed. To confirm that you have the necessary permission scope, you can check the scope returned by the /tt_user/token_info/get/ endpoint. If the required permission has not been granted to you, follow the steps outlined in Authorization to enable the TikTok account user to reauthorize your app with the permission. Supported fields : item_id : Unique identifier for the video. thumbnail_url : Preview thumbnail URL for the video. share_url : A shareable URL for the video. embed_url : An embeddable URL for the video. caption : The caption/description for the video. video_duration : Duration of the video, in seconds. likes : Likes. The total number of likes the video has received. comments : Comments. The total number of comments the video has received. shares : Shares. The total number of times the video has been shared. favorites : Favorites. The total number of times the video has been added to favorites. create_time : Unix/epoch date-time when the video was posted. reach : Reach. The number of people who watched your published content at least once. video_views : Video views. The number of times viewers watched your video. Note : Counts when playback duration >0 and the playback is the first playback in an impression session. If the user swipes away from the ad then swipes back, it would be counted as 2 impressions. Therefore, a new video view will be counted again with the new impression session. total_time_watched : Total play time. The amount of time viewers spent watching your video. average_time_watched : Average watch time. The average time viewers spent watching your video. full_video_watched_rate : Watched full video rate. The percentage of viewers who finish watching your video. new_followers : New followers. The number of viewers who started following you. profile_views : Profile views. The total number of profile views from users who visited through your video. website_clicks : Website clicks. The total number of clicks on your website link from users who visited your profile page through your video. phone_number_clicks : Phone number clicks. The total number of clicks on your phone number link from users who visited your profile page through your video. lead_submissions : Lead submissions. The total number of leads (e.g. price quotes, newsletter subscriptions, etc.) collected from your consumers who visited your profile page through your video. app_download_clicks : App download link clicks. The total number of clicks on your app download link from users who visited your profile page through your video. email_clicks : Email clicks. The total number of times people have clicked the Email button on your profile after watching this specific video. address_clicks : Address clicks. The total number of times people have clicked the Address button on your profile after watching this specific video. video_view_retention : Audience retention. This metric indicates how many of your viewers are still watching after a certain amount of time. impression_sources : Traffic source. This metric helps you understand the breakdown of traffic sources for those who viewed your video. audience_genders : Gender. The distribution of your viewers by gender. This data is based on factors including the information viewers provide. audience_countries : Top countries. The distribution of your viewers by the top countries or regions. This data is based on factors including the information viewers provide. audience_cities : Top cities. The distribution of your viewers by the top cities. This data is based on factors including the information viewers provide. audience_types : Viewer types. The breakdown of your audience into new viewers versus returning viewers, and followers versus non-followers. engagement_likes : Engagement likes. The distribution of your viewers who liked your video at specific points in the video's timeline.

parameters.name: filters
parameters.description: Filters to apply to the result set.

parameters.name: video_ids
parameters.description: A list of video IDs to filter the insights for. Example : ["6995316737801538821", "8015388216995316737"] .

parameters.name: ad_post_only
parameters.description: Valid only when video_ids is specified. Whether to filter videos ( video_ids ) to include only those that have been used as Spark Ads. Supported values: true , false . Default value: false .

parameters.name: cursor
parameters.description: Cursor for pagination. If the response parameter has_more is true, pass the returned cursor in this parameter in the subsequent request to receive the next page of results. Default value : Current time as Epoch/Unix timestamp in milliseconds. Note : The cursor value is a UTC Unix timestamp in milliseconds. You can pass in a customized timestamp to fetch the user's videos posted before the provided timestamp.

parameters.name: max_count
parameters.description: The maximum number of videos that will be returned for each page. Default value : 10 Maximum value : 20 Note : Due to our trust and safety policies, it is possible that the endpoint returns less than max_count number of videos even if the response parameter has_more is true.

top_fields.name: Date
top_fields.description: Date and time (GMT) when the response was received. Example : Fri, 13 Aug 2021 08:04:42 GMT

top_fields.name: X-Tt-Logid
top_fields.description: Unique identifier for the API request.

item_fields.name: request_id
item_fields.description: Unique identifier for the API request. Note : Please record this field for all API requests. Important for issue reports and troubleshooting.

item_fields.name: code
item_fields.description: Response code. For the complete list of response codes and descriptions, see Appendix - Return Codes .

item_fields.name: message
item_fields.description: Response message. For details, see Appendix - Return Codes .

item_fields.name: data
item_fields.description: Return data

item_fields.name: videos
item_fields.description: The list of public video posts of the TikTok account, including organic videos displayed in the account's profile, as well as "Only show in ads" video posts (video posts used exclusively as ads that do not appear in the TikTok account's profile but are publicly accessible as ads).

item_fields.name: item_id
item_fields.description: Unique identifier for the video. Example : 6995316737801538821 Updated in : Real-time

item_fields.name: thumbnail_url
item_fields.description: Temporary URL for thumbnail of video content. Expiration date-time included in x-expires query param as Epoch/Unix time in seconds. Example : https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/tos-maliva-avt-0068/75dec21d63500917fb6ec8bc59415156~c5_300x300.jpeg?x-expires=1614099600&x-signature=PmK%2BWs3LzSzRL2tYs%2FZx7EjG3Gk%3D Updated in : Real-time

item_fields.name: share_url
item_fields.description: A shareable URL for this TikTok video. Note that the website behaves differently on Mobile and Desktop devices. Example : https://www.tiktok.com/@feather_in_the_w1nd/video/6994189750940863749?utm_campaign=tt4d_open_api&utm_source=6945731504177676290 Updated in : Real-time

item_fields.name: embed_url
item_fields.description: An embeddable link for this TikTok video. This URL can be used to embed the TikTok video in external websites or applications. If the privacy setting of the post is "Friends" or "Only you", the video will not be viewable through this link. Example : https://www.tiktok.com/player/v1/1234567891234567891?music_info=1&description=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&utm_campaign=tt4d_open_api&utm_source=1234567891234567891 Updated in : Real-time

item_fields.name: caption
item_fields.description: Video description. Example : Nuki: me and me casa ðŸ  #cat #kitten #britishshorthair Updated in : Real-time

item_fields.name: video_duration
item_fields.description: Video length - in seconds, up to three decimal places. Example : 20.001 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: likes
item_fields.description: Likes. Total number of likes on the video. Example : 243 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: comments
item_fields.description: Comments. Total number of comments on the video. Example : 10 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: shares
item_fields.description: Shares. Total number of times the video has been shared. The share count displayed in this field corresponds to the number of shares shown in the For You feed on the TikTok mobile app. It includes both external shares and internal shares sent to friends using the "Send to friends" button. For example, if a video is shared externally 30 times and shared with friends within the TikTok app 20 times, the value of this field will be 50. Example : 10 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: favorites
item_fields.description: Favorites. The total number of times the video has been added to favorites. Data source : Business Analytics. Example : 10 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: create_time
item_fields.description: Unix/epoch date-time when the video was posted, in UTC time-zone. Example :1628461703 Updated in : Real-time

item_fields.name: reach
item_fields.description: Reach. The number of people who watched your published content at least once. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : 136 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: video_views
item_fields.description: Video views. The number of times viewers watched your video. Note : Counts when playback duration >0 and the playback is the first playback in an impression session. If the user swipes away from the ad then swipes back, it would be counted as 2 impressions. Therefore, a new video view will be counted again with the new impression session. Example : 603 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: total_time_watched
item_fields.description: Total play time. The amount of time viewers spent watching your video, in seconds. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : 587.024 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: average_time_watched
item_fields.description: Average watch time. The average time viewers spent watching your video, in seconds. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : 3.862 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: full_video_watched_rate
item_fields.description: Watched full video rate. The percentage of viewers who finish watching your video. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : 0.0395 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: new_followers
item_fields.description: New followers. The number of viewers who started following you. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : 123 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: profile_views
item_fields.description: Profile views. The total number of profile views from users who visited through your video. Data source : Business Analytics. Example : 123 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time) Note : The data for this metric is only available for Business Accounts.

item_fields.name: website_clicks
item_fields.description: Website clicks. The total number of clicks on your website link from users who visited your profile page through your video. Data source : Business Analytics. Example : 123 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time) Note : The data for this metric is only available for Registered Business Accounts .

item_fields.name: phone_number_clicks
item_fields.description: Phone number clicks. The total number of clicks on your phone number link from users who visited your profile page through your video. Data source : Business Analytics. Example : 123 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time) Note : The data for this metric is only available for Registered Business Accounts .

item_fields.name: lead_submissions
item_fields.description: Lead submissions. The total number of leads (e.g. price quotes, newsletter subscriptions, etc.) collected from your consumers who visited your profile page through your video. Data source : Business Analytics. Example : 123 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time) Note : The data for this metric is only available for Registered Business Accounts .

item_fields.name: app_download_clicks
item_fields.description: App download link clicks. The total number of clicks on your app download link from users who visited your profile page through your video. Data source : Business Analytics. Example : 123 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time) Note : The data for this metric is only available for Registered Business Accounts .

item_fields.name: email_clicks
item_fields.description: Email clicks. The total number of times people have clicked the Email button on your profile after watching this specific video. Data source : Business Analytics. Example : 123 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time) Note : The data for this metric is only available for Registered Business Accounts .

item_fields.name: address_clicks
item_fields.description: Address clicks. The total number of times people have clicked the Address button on your profile after watching this specific video. Data source : Business Analytics. Example : 123 Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time) Note : The data for this metric is only available for Registered Business Accounts .

item_fields.name: video_view_retention
item_fields.description: Audience retention. This metric indicates how many of your viewers are still watching after a certain amount of time. Data source : TikTok Studio. Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: second
item_fields.description: A specific second in the video's timeline.

item_fields.name: percentage
item_fields.description: The percentage of viewers who are still watching your video at the specific second.

item_fields.name: impression_sources
item_fields.description: Traffic source. This metric shows the places where your viewers discover your posts and helps you understand the breakdown of traffic sources for those who viewed your video, ranked from the largest contribution to the smallest. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : [{impression_source: "For You", percentage: 0.7554 }, {impression_source: "Follow", percentage: 0.2445 }, ...] Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: impression_source
item_fields.description: The traffic source type. Enum values: For You : For You feed. Follow : Follow feed. Sound : sound pages. Personal Profile : profile pages.. Search : search pages. Others : others. Direct Message : direct message. Note : The availability of the Direct Message value depends on whether you can see the corresponding data within TikTok Studio. If the corresponding data is missing from TikTok Studio, you will not be able to get the data.

item_fields.name: percentage
item_fields.description: The percentage of views from the source type.

item_fields.name: audience_genders
item_fields.description: Gender. The distribution of your viewers by gender. This data is based on factors including the information viewers provide. Data source : TikTok Studio. Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: gender
item_fields.description: Gender. Enum values: Female , Male , Other .

item_fields.name: percentage
item_fields.description: Percentage of viewers associated with the gender.

item_fields.name: audience_countries
item_fields.description: Top countries or regions. The distribution of your viewers by the top countries or regions. This data is based on factors including the information viewers provide. Max size : 10. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : [{"country":"CA","percentage":0.0132}, {"country":"GB","percentage":0.0987},{"country":"US","percentage":0.7303}, ...] Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: country
item_fields.description: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country or region code.

item_fields.name: percentage
item_fields.description: Percentage of viewers registered from a country or region.

item_fields.name: audience_cities
item_fields.description: Top cities. The distribution of your viewers by the top cities. This data is based on factors including the information viewers provide. Max size : 10. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : [{"city_name": "US Cincinnati","percentage": 0.597},{"city_name": "US Los Angeles","percentage": 0.597},{"city_name": "US Other","percentage": 17.4921},{"city_name": "US Ashburn","percentage": 1.2139}] Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: city_name
item_fields.description: City name. Example : US Cincinnati.

item_fields.name: percentage
item_fields.description: Percentage of viewers associated with the city. Example : 1.2139

item_fields.name: audience_types
item_fields.description: Viewer types. The breakdown of your audience into new viewers versus returning viewers, and followers versus non-followers. Data source : TikTok Studio. Example : [{"percentage": 0,"type": "FOLLOWER_PERCENT"},{"percentage": 0.98,"type": "NEW_VIEWER"},{"percentage": 1,"type": "NON_FOLLOWER_PERCENT"},{"percentage": 0.02,"type": "RETURN_VIEWER"}] Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: type
item_fields.description: Audience type. Enum values: NEW_VIEWER : New viewers. Viewers who are either viewing a post from you for the first time, or it has been a year since they last viewed your posts. RETURN_VIEWER : Returning viewers. Viewers who have viewed your posts in the past year. FOLLOWER_PERCENT : Followers. Viewers who are following you on TikTok. NON_FOLLOWER_PERCENT : Non-followers. Viewers who are not following you on TikTok.

item_fields.name: percentage
item_fields.description: Percentage of viewers associated with the audience type.

item_fields.name: engagement_likes
item_fields.description: Engagement likes. The distribution of your viewers who liked your video at specific points in the video's timeline. Data source : TikTok Studio. Updated in : T + 24-48 hrs (UTC time)

item_fields.name: second
item_fields.description: A specific second in the video's timeline.

item_fields.name: percentage
item_fields.description: Percentage of viewers who liked your video at the specific second.

item_fields.name: cursor
item_fields.description: Cursor for the next page of results, to be passed in the cursor query parameter of the subsequent API request. Updated in : Real-time

item_fields.name: has_more
item_fields.description: Whether an additional page of data is available. Updated in : Real-time
